docs.abstract: President Trump said his description of some immigrants as ‘animals’ referred to MS-13 members. But his remarks came during a discussion on how to prosecute immigrants in sanctuary cities, which don’t protect gang members who committed horrific crimes.

docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump’s “animals” comment came during a White House discussion on Wednesday about so-called sanctuary cities. He was responding to Sheriff Margaret Mims, of Fresno County, Calif., who had recounted how California state laws were holding her back from cooperating with deportation efforts by federal Immigration and Customs Enforcement agents.
